# VARIABLES                                                             00450000
A VARIABLE IS AN ELEMENT DERCLARED IN A PROGRAM TO STORE A VALUE        00460000
IT CAN BE EITHER A CHARACTER STRING OR A NUMBER                         00470000
TWO SECTION                                                             00480000
       - FILE SECTION                                                   00490000
       - WORKING STORAGE SECTION                                        00500000
EVERY VARIABLE DECLARATION STARTS WITH A LEVEL NUMBER, THIS ORGANIZES   00510000
VARIABLES HIERARCHICALLY                                                00520000
LEVEL 01 IS THE HIGHEST                                                 00530000
01 - 49                                                                 00540000
IT MUST START WITH A LETTER                                             00550000
IT MUST NOT EXCEED 30 CHARS                                             00560000
ONLY LETTERS,DIGITS,HYPHENS ALLOWED                                     00570000
NOT RESERVED WORDS                                                      00580000
